        "title": "[codex] Add local ClawSweeper review workflow",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nAdds a local ClawSweeper review workflow for maintainers who want advisory output before PR submission or re-review.  This was based on a discussion with @joshavant on discord\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- Add `pnpm run review:local` for read-only local issue/PR review without the starter GitHub comment.\r\n- Add `pnpm run codex:local:check` to verify local Codex CLI auth and execution without printing secrets.\r\n- Preserve local Codex auth only for `--local-only`; hosted/normal workers still strip Codex/OpenAI/GitHub write credentials.\r\n- Prefer the Windows Codex app binary for local-only review and support Node-shebang Codex shims on Windows.\r\n- Add `.agents/skills/local-clawsweeper-review` as an optional ergonomic Codex wrapper.\r\n- Add `docs/local-clawsweeper-review.md`, including one-PR-at-a-time setup, CLI auth, clean target checkout guidance, and embedded optional skill contents.\r\n\r\n## Validation\r\n\r\n- `pnpm run build:all`\r\n- `python C:\\Users\\marti\\.codex\\skills\\.system\\skill-creator\\scripts\\quick_validate.py .agents\\skills\\local-clawsweeper-review`\r\n- `pnpm run codex:local:check`\r\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check scripts/check-local-codex.mjs src/clawsweeper.ts test/clawsweeper.test.ts test/codex-process.test.ts`\r\n- `pnpm run lint:src`\r\n- `pnpm run lint:scripts`\r\n- `node --test test\\codex-process.test.ts`\r\n- `node --test --test-name-pattern \"runCodex honors env login config|review command leaves Codex login method|Codex login method\" test\\clawsweeper.test.ts`\r\n- `node --test --test-name-pattern \"runCodex accepts valid structured output after non-zero Codex exit\" test\\clawsweeper.test.ts`\r\n- Local review proof: `pnpm run review:local -- --target-repo openclaw/openclaw --target-dir C:\\oc-work\\clawsweeper-local-target-openclaw --item-number 96138 --batch-size 1 --shard-count 1 --max-pages 1 --artifact-dir C:\\oc-work\\clawsweeper-source\\artifacts\\local-review-96138-cleanbranch-20260623 --codex-model gpt-5.5 --codex-reasoning-effort high --codex-timeout-ms 600000`\r\n\r\nLocal review result for #96138: `review_status=complete`, `decision=keep_open`, `confidence=high`, `review_service_tier=fast`; starter comment was skipped.\r\n\r\nNote: `pnpm run test:unit` on this Windows checkout currently hits an existing CRLF-sensitive workflow fixture assertion; the previous Linux CI run reached coverage and only failed `format:check` on `scripts/check-local-codex.mjs` and `src/clawsweeper.ts`, which are now covered by the touched-file format check above.",
